{#
  /sanctions/sector/<slug> — A–Z directory of every OFAC SDN
  designation classified into one sector (military / economic /
  diplomatic / governance).

  Sister page to /sanctions/<bucket> — same A–Z UX, but pivoted on
  sector instead of entity-type. The H1 deliberately uses the word
  "currently" to match the GSC query that motivated this page
  ("ofac sdn list current military, economic, diplomatic"); freshness
  copy reinforces it.

  Each name links to the same /sanctions/<bucket>/<slug> profile that
  the bucket-based index links to — one profile, two paths in.
#}
{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}
{% from "_cluster_nav.html.j2" import cluster_nav %}

{% block content %}
<div class="container-wide">
  <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href="/sanctions-tracker">OFAC Venezuela Sanctions</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href="/sanctions/by-sector">By sector</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <strong>{{ sector_label }}</strong>
  </nav>

  <article>
    <header>
      <div style="font-size:12px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1.4px; color:var(--sr-red); font-weight:700;">
        Live tracker · {{ today_human }} · {{ profiles|length }} active designations
      </div>
      <h1>OFAC Venezuela SDN — Currently Sanctioned {{ sector_label }} ({{ profiles|length }})</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        Every {{ sector_label|lower }} on the US Treasury OFAC SDN List under
        Venezuela-related sanctions programs. Each name links to a permanent
        profile with biographical data, OFAC program code, and source link.
      </p>
      <div class="meta">
        <span><strong>Source:</strong> US Treasury OFAC SDN List</span>
        <span><strong>Refreshed:</strong> twice daily (10am &amp; 5pm Medellín)</span>
        <span><strong>Programs covered:</strong> VENEZUELA, EO 13692, EO 13850, EO 13884</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="cr-search-panel" role="search" aria-label="Search sanctioned {{ sector_label|lower }}">
      <label class="cr-search-label" for="sector-directory-search">Search this sector list</label>
      <div class="cr-search-row">
        <input type="search" id="sector-directory-search" placeholder="Type a name, program, DOB, IMO, aircraft tail…" autocomplete="off">
      </div>
      <p class="cr-search-help">This filters the {{ profiles|length }} active {{ sector_label|lower }} below.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="body">
      <div class="takeaways">
        <h3>What "{{ sector_label|lower }}" means here</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 14px;">{{ sector_description }}</p>
      </div>

      <p>
        Switch between sector views:
      </p>
      <ul>
        {% for s in sectors_nav %}
        <li>
          {% if s.key == active_key %}
          <strong>{{ s.label }} ({{ s.count }})</strong> — current view
          {% else %}
          <a href="{{ s.url_path }}"><strong>{{ s.label }}</strong></a> ({{ s.count }})
          {% endif %}
        </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>

      <h2>All {{ sector_label|lower }} (A–Z)</h2>
      <div class="cr-empty-filter" id="sector-directory-empty">No {{ sector_label|lower }} match that search.</div>
      {% if grouped %}
      {% for letter, items in grouped %}
      <h3 id="{{ letter }}">{{ letter }}</h3>
      <ul class="related">
        {% for p in items %}
        <li data-search="{{ (p.display_name ~ ' ' ~ p.raw_name ~ ' ' ~ (p.program or '') ~ ' ' ~ p.category_singular ~ ' ' ~ (p.parsed.dob or '') ~ ' ' ~ (p.parsed.imo or '') ~ ' ' ~ (p.parsed.aircraft_tail or ''))|lower }}">
          <a href="{{ p.url_path }}">{{ p.display_name }}</a>
          <small>— {{ p.program or 'VENEZUELA' }} ·
            {{ p.category_singular }}{% if p.parsed.dob %} · DOB {{ p.parsed.dob }}{% elif p.parsed.imo %} · IMO {{ p.parsed.imo }}{% elif p.parsed.aircraft_tail %} · Tail {{ p.parsed.aircraft_tail }}{% endif %}</small>
        </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
      {% endfor %}
      {% else %}
      <p>No designations are currently classified under this sector.</p>
      {% endif %}

      <h2>Why this view exists</h2>
      <p>
        OFAC publishes the Venezuela SDN list grouped only by entity type
        (individuals / entities / vessels / aircraft) and by executive order.
        Compliance, M&amp;A, and journalist research workflows usually want a
        sector-pivoted view — "who are the currently-sanctioned military
        officials?" or "which Venezuelan banks are blocked?" — which neither
        OFAC nor most trackers offer. We compute the sector for every
        designation from its OFAC remarks plus a curated overrides table; see
        the <a href="/sanctions/by-sector">sector overview page</a> for the full
        methodology.
      </p>

      <h2>Verifying these designations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://sanctions-search.ofac.treasury.gov/" rel="nofollow">OFAC official Sanctions Search</a> — primary source for live screening</li>
        <li><a href="/tools/ofac-venezuela-sanctions-checker">Our search tool</a> — paste any name to see if it's currently designated</li>
        <li><a href="/tools/ofac-venezuela-general-licenses">Active OFAC General Licenses for Venezuela</a></li>
        <li><a href="/explainers/what-are-ofac-sanctions-on-venezuela">What are OFAC sanctions on Venezuela? (plain-English guide)</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>

  {{ cluster_nav(cluster_ctx) }}
</div>

<script>
(function () {
  var input = document.getElementById('sector-directory-search');
  var empty = document.getElementById('sector-directory-empty');
  if (!input) return;
  var lists = Array.prototype.slice.call(document.querySelectorAll('ul.related'));
  input.addEventListener('input', function () {
    var q = input.value.trim().toLowerCase();
    var totalVisible = 0;
    lists.forEach(function (list) {
      var visibleInList = 0;
      Array.prototype.slice.call(list.querySelectorAll('li[data-search]')).forEach(function (li) {
        var show = !q || (li.getAttribute('data-search') || '').indexOf(q) !== -1;
        li.style.display = show ? '' : 'none';
        if (show) visibleInList += 1;
      });
      totalVisible += visibleInList;
      list.style.display = visibleInList ? '' : 'none';
      var heading = list.previousElementSibling;
      if (heading && heading.tagName === 'H3') heading.style.display = visibleInList ? '' : 'none';
    });
    if (empty) empty.style.display = q && totalVisible === 0 ? 'block' : 'none';
  });
})();
</script>
{% endblock %}
